    "visualization_explanation": "This dataset contains three categorical proportions representing Earth's hydrosphere composition. The synthetic data follows known scientific estimates (USGS) with saltwater at 97\u00b10.5%, ice caps/glaciers at 2\u00b10.3%, and liquid freshwater at 1\u00b10.2%. The pie chart maximizes data-ink ratio by removing unnecessary gridlines while maintaining Cairo's effectiveness principles through: 1) Color contrast between water types 2) Immediate visual hierarchy through slice separation 3) Percentage annotations maintaining magnitude relationships. The 100% summation and explicit percentage formatting create strong statistical anchors, with interactive elements maintaining Tufte's principle of showing detail on demand."
